cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of Alchemist, a tool for distributed machine learning, on supercomputers and with various data analysis frameworks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of HPC simulations, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The discussion of data transfer times suggests a focus on optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
